## MathNaryOperator class

 Specifies an N-ary mathematical object, such as Summation and Integral.
 It consists of an operator, a base (or operand), and optional upper and lower limits. 
 Examples of N-ary operators are: Summation, Union, Intersection, Integral 
 
| [MathNaryOperator]([char], [MathLimit], [MathLimit], [MathLimit]) | Initializes a new instance of the MathNaryOperator class. |

| Name | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| operatorSymbol | [char] | Nary operator symbol |
| baseArgument | [MathLimit] | Base argument |
| lowerLimit | [MathLimit] | Lower limit |
| upperLimit | [MathLimit] | Upper limit |
